-- Cardinals Beat Nationals 12-4 to Even MLB Playoff Series at 1-1
-- B y   R o b   G l o s t e r
-- 2012-10-09T00:07:35Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-10-09/cardinals-beat-nationals-12-4-to-even-mlb-playoff-series-at-1-1.html
Carlos Beltran  hit two home runs and
the host St. Louis Cardinals defeated the Washington Nationals
12-4 to even their Major League Baseball playoff series at one
game each.  Game 3 of the best-of-five National League Division Series
is set for Oct. 10 in Washington.  The winner of the series will face the  Cincinnati Reds  or
the San Francisco Giants in the NL Championship Series. The Reds
lead the Giants 2-0 in their division series.  The New York Yankees try to take a 2-0 lead in their AL
Division Series tonight when they play at the Baltimore Orioles,
if the weather allows. Rain is forecast throughout the evening
in Baltimore and the start of the game has been delayed.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Rob Gloster at 
 rgloster@bloomberg.net  